## Caveats

We need to have some caveats in mind while interpreting the data. These data do not include population in  "institutional household": for example, old-peopleâ€™s homes, orphanages, hospitals, boarding schools, hotels, hostels and guest houses, institutions for persons with disabilities, prisons, monasteries, convents, military and police barracks, and camps for workers.  

Another caveat is the lack of information on the timeframe of migration. Without this information, it is difficult to interpret the recency of these patterns and how they change over time.  
